  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-03-30",
    "date": "2023-12-12T15:48:16Z",
    "text": "Gun Trafficker Detection Act\n\nThis bill requires gun owners to report the theft or loss of a firearm to law enforcement within 48 hours. A violation is subject to criminal and civil penalties.\n\nAdditionally, the bill requires states to use at least 5% of funds under the Edward Byrne Memorial Justice Assistance Grant program to implement effective management and collection of data related to lost or stolen firearms that are reported to law enforcement."
